284
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,119
Tempura!

285
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,640
With good food,

286
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:21,640
how can there not be good sake?

287
00:22:24,119 --> 00:22:25,759
It's too cold.

288
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:27,119
So,

289
00:22:27,119 --> 00:22:28,880
could you get me a bottle of Japanese sake?

290
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,160
Just one bottle is enough.

291
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,720
Thank you.

292
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,440
You know,

293
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,119
ever since I met you,

294
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:46,559
I've known where my future path lies.

295
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,880
Because you gave me hope.

296
00:22:53,759 --> 00:22:54,720
I want to protect you.

297
00:22:56,759 --> 00:22:58,279
I stayed by Old Xie's side

298
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:00,279
because I was afraid that if one day

299
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:02,559
he discovered your true identity,

300
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,039
he would try to harm you.

301
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:05,920
I need to keep an eye on him.

302
00:23:07,119 --> 00:23:08,599
If that day really comes,

303
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,720
I will do everything I can to protect you.

304
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,480
Because I promised you.

305
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,440
I want to make sure you leave safely.

306
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,559
Maybe this

307
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,480
is the reason I keep going now.

308
00:23:27,519 --> 00:23:28,319
Nian Ci

309
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:32,960
The mission isn't complete.

310
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,319
I won't leave.

311
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,559
I know what you're thinking.

312
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,599
But you need to understand,

313
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,079
Every day that I can close my eyes

314
00:23:43,599 --> 00:23:44,640
and open them again

315
00:23:45,599 --> 00:23:47,319
is already a luxury.

316
00:23:48,839 --> 00:23:50,440
Of course I know that.

317
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,599
When the country is in peril,

318
00:23:54,279 --> 00:23:55,279
how can there be a home?

319
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,759
But do you know

320
00:23:58,759 --> 00:24:00,960
I just want to face it together with you,

321
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,920
to fight by your side until the end,

322
00:24:03,599 --> 00:24:04,759
even if it means dying.

323
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,200
I still want to be with you.

324
00:24:10,519 --> 00:24:11,680
I just don't know

325
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:14,119
how long Old Tan will keep testing me.

326
00:24:16,799 --> 00:24:18,839
Tests always take some time.

327
00:24:20,119 --> 00:24:21,160
Be patient.

328
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:23,759
I'll wait.

329
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:25,599
I'll prove

330
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:28,119
my faith isn't just a momentary passion.

331
00:24:29,039 --> 00:24:31,599
I want to become a true comrade with you.

332
00:24:31,759 --> 00:24:32,799
A fellow soldier.

333
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:34,799
Once the mission is complete,

334
00:24:36,319 --> 00:24:37,759
we'll return to Yan'an together.

335
00:24:41,039 --> 00:24:41,839
Alright.

336
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:46,000
As long as we're alive.

337
00:25:09,279 --> 00:25:11,079
You can't even deliver wine properly.

338
00:25:11,119 --> 00:25:12,359
I'm sorry.

339
00:25:12,359 --> 00:25:13,759
Are you an idiot?

340
00:25:13,759 --> 00:25:15,039
Hurry up and clean this up.

341
00:25:46,599 --> 00:25:48,319
It's over, it's over, it's over.

342
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:49,720
Quick, report to Chief Mizuno.

343
00:26:06,079 --> 00:26:10,000
The tree wishes to be still

344
00:26:10,759 --> 00:26:13,880
but the wind does not cease.

345
00:26:15,759 --> 00:26:17,000
Mizuno.

346
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,839
Farewell.

347
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,200
Stop the car.

348
00:26:45,359 --> 00:26:46,519
Stop right there.

349
00:26:46,759 --> 00:26:48,240
Block him.

350
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,000
Chief.

351
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,759
The prisoner has escaped from jail.

352
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,440
What are you all doing?

353
00:27:43,279 --> 00:27:44,880
Is the information accurate?

354
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:45,680
Don't worry.

355
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,839
I've already sent our men to follow him.

356
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,200
He's definitely here.

357
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,680
Director Cui.

358
00:27:57,279 --> 00:27:57,880
Chief.

359
00:27:58,039 --> 00:27:59,039
There's a situation.

360
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,039
It seems someone has escaped.

361
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:02,880
The Japanese side is already in chaos.

362
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:05,720
Tell our people

363
00:28:05,839 --> 00:28:08,000
to keep a close watch on the nearby streets.

364
00:28:08,279 --> 00:28:09,079
Yes.

365
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,079
Go.

366
00:28:10,079 --> 00:28:10,880
Yes.

367
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,680
Do you think our luck

368
00:28:17,759 --> 00:28:19,279
could really be this good?

369
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,799
We just got here,

370
00:28:21,039 --> 00:28:22,599
and Asai Hisashi already escaped.

371
00:28:23,119 --> 00:28:23,920
Chief.

372
00:28:24,079 --> 00:28:26,359
This is what they call "timing is better than being early."

373
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:28,240
Now it all depends on the Japanese

374
00:28:28,319 --> 00:28:30,160
whether they'll let us get involved in this matter.

375
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:32,079
As long as we have a reason,

376
00:28:32,359 --> 00:28:34,119
why would we worry about not being able to get involved?

377
00:28:34,759 --> 00:28:35,720
It seems

378
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:38,400
I should meet this Mizuno myself.

379
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:39,680
Yes.

380
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:49,440
Such a heavily guarded military police prison

381
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,480
how did it let an unarmed old man

382
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,240
escape?

383
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:52,599
I deserve to be punished.

384
00:28:52,599 --> 00:28:53,920
I was careless.

385
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:54,799
Even though we switched the utensils to wooden ones,

386
00:28:54,799 --> 00:28:56,240
he still found a loophole.

387
00:29:13,599 --> 00:29:14,319
Chief,

388
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:16,039
the Special Operations Headquarters has arrived.

389
00:29:43,079 --> 00:29:43,880
Director Li,

390
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:45,519
you're usually so busy,

391
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,119
but today you have some free time.

392
00:29:47,279 --> 00:29:48,799
What's with all this commotion?

393
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,039
There's no other way.

394
00:29:50,519 --> 00:29:51,759
The higher-ups have given us heavy tasks.

395
00:29:51,759 --> 00:29:53,000
The responsibility on my shoulders is great.

396
00:29:53,279 --> 00:29:55,119
I have to handle things personally.

397
00:29:55,119 --> 00:29:56,359
So I came here myself.

398
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,920
The Special Operations Headquarters has a new mission.

399
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,279
How come I haven't heard about it?

400
00:30:00,359 --> 00:30:02,599
Mr. Mizuno, you really are forgetful.

401
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:03,359
The first wave

402
00:30:03,359 --> 00:30:05,839
of the joint announcement to capture the fugitive Asai Shou

403
00:30:05,839 --> 00:30:07,200
has already been released.

404
00:30:07,519 --> 00:30:08,119
Here,

405
00:30:08,119 --> 00:30:10,480
let Mr. Mizuno take a look.

406
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:12,119
Of course I know about this.

407
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,759
But bringing the fugitive search here,

408
00:30:14,839 --> 00:30:15,640
what does that mean?

409
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:17,839
You're blaming me again.

410
00:30:18,240 --> 00:30:19,400
How would I dare to suspect

411
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,920
that Mr. Mizuno is harboring a fugitive?

412
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:24,640
We just heard the news ourselves.

413
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:26,920
They said there are traces of the suspect nearby.

414
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:29,079
So I brought some people to try our luck.

415
00:30:29,519 --> 00:30:30,920
Unexpectedly, as soon as we arrived,

416
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,839
it really does seem like something is going on.

417
00:30:35,839 --> 00:30:38,400
It's just that one deserter ran away from under my command.

418
00:30:38,519 --> 00:30:39,720
But Director Li,

419
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:42,319
you made such a big fuss over just a rumor.

420
00:30:42,319 --> 00:30:43,759
You even came in person.

421
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:44,960
I didn't expect that.

422
00:30:45,599 --> 00:30:47,279
Are you always this spontaneous?

423
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,880
I wouldn't say spontaneous.

424
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,039
I just like to take risks.

425
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,000
If I'm lucky today,

426
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:54,440
it would be a great achievement for both me and the new government.

427
00:30:54,559 --> 00:30:56,519
That would be a huge accomplishment.

428
00:30:58,240 --> 00:31:00,119
Since this is a search operation,

429
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,119
what are we waiting for?

430
00:31:03,079 --> 00:31:04,279
We Chinese

431
00:31:04,279 --> 00:31:05,640
value proper etiquette.

432
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:08,079
So we should at least say hello when we arrive.

433
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:09,680
Since Mr. Mizuno

434
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,759
has already stationed troops here,

435
00:31:11,799 --> 00:31:13,440
I can rest assured.

436
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:16,519
We'll search and set up defenses nearby.

437
00:31:17,319 --> 00:31:18,440
Who knows,

438
00:31:18,759 --> 00:31:20,400
we might even help Mr. Mizuno

439
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,319
find that deserter.

440
00:31:22,319 --> 00:31:23,400
Yes, yes.

441
00:31:26,119 --> 00:31:27,279
Well then, Mr. Mizuno,

442
00:31:28,519 --> 00:31:29,680
sorry to trouble you.

443
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,440
Let's find a place nearby

444
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,240
and set up our office here.

445
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,359
Call Liang Shuo over.

446
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:37,039
Yes.

447
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,000
Let's go.

448
00:31:42,559 --> 00:31:43,359
Let's go too.

449
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,319
Chief,

450
00:31:55,559 --> 00:31:56,960
what should I do?

451
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,799
They really came at just the right time.

452
00:32:00,359 --> 00:32:02,119
Who leaked the information?

453
00:32:13,039 --> 00:32:14,680
Judging by Shingen Mizuno's reaction,

454
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:16,359
I can conclude

455
00:32:16,799 --> 00:32:18,119
that your guess

456
00:32:18,119 --> 00:32:20,200
is most likely correct.

457
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:23,599
And as for the deserter who escaped,

458
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,039
it's a clear case of trying to cover things up.

459
00:32:27,359 --> 00:32:28,240
What a pity.

460
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:29,920
We were a step too late.

461
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,759
Not late at all.

462
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:33,240
We couldn't have

463
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:35,039
searched in front of Shingen Mizuno.

464
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,400
The situation is still unclear.

465
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,920
That actually gives us an opportunity.

466
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,240
Toshi Asai has escaped.

467
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:43,279
Now everyone has a chance to catch him.

468
00:32:43,559 --> 00:32:44,960
The opportunity is open to all.

469
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,279
It's equal for everyone.

470
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:47,480
So,

471
00:32:48,359 --> 00:32:49,720
from now on,

472
00:32:50,359 --> 00:32:51,720
capturing Toshi Asai

473
00:32:52,079 --> 00:32:54,880
is our top priority.

474
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,559
What are you daydreaming about?

475
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,720
Sister-in-law, you startled me.

476
00:33:28,799 --> 00:33:30,079
You...

477
00:33:30,079 --> 00:33:31,519
If you keep being so quiet,

478
00:33:31,799 --> 00:33:33,960
I'll start thinking you're sick.

479
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,400
No, I'm not.

480
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,160
When was I not talking?

481
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,960
I can tell.

482
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,000
You have something on your mind.

483
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,279
What's wrong?

484
00:33:45,039 --> 00:33:46,240
Is it that rascal Liang Shuo

485
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,240
bullying you again?

486
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:48,519
No.

487
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,000
He's been so busy these past couple of days

488
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,960
that he's pulled two all-nighters at headquarters.

489
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:54,279
I haven't even seen him.

490
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,759
How could he have time to bully me?

491
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,720
That's how men are.

492
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,519
They always get like this when they're working.

493
00:34:01,559 --> 00:34:03,200
Old Cui is the same these days.

494
00:34:03,519 --> 00:34:04,960
He just got home yesterday,

495
00:34:05,119 --> 00:34:07,119
and then headquarters called him away again.

496
00:34:07,559 --> 00:34:09,519
He barely had time to sit down.

497
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:12,440
He didn't even have time to say a word to me.

498
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:14,079
So about your pregnancy,

499
00:34:14,079 --> 00:34:15,320
Brother Cui still doesn't know?

500
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:18,840
Something this important

501
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:20,840
you have to find the right time

502
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:22,639
to sit down and talk to him properly.

503
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,039
Something this important

504
00:34:24,119 --> 00:34:25,360
really needs to be discussed properly.

505
00:34:48,039 --> 00:34:49,239
Mr. Li is here.

506
00:34:49,239 --> 00:34:49,880
Yes.

507
00:34:50,039 --> 00:34:52,639
Last time, I had a great conversation with Miss Xie.

508
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:54,199
I wonder if she could

509
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:56,159
recommend a few more products to me.

510
00:34:57,519 --> 00:34:59,079
Madam, all the goods in the back have been checked.

511
00:34:59,079 --> 00:35:00,480
Please come over and take a look.

512
00:35:01,679 --> 00:35:03,920
Mr. Li, I'll excuse myself for now.

513
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,400
Yuxin,

514
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,519
please quickly recommend some more products to Mr. Li.

515
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:09,840
Okay, I'll be right there.

516
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,000
You really fit the role of a good friend.

517
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:22,880
You played it quite well.

518
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:25,400
I'll take that as a compliment.

519
00:35:26,599 --> 00:35:27,400
Go ahead.

520
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:29,800
Any new updates from Liang Shuo?

521
00:35:30,239 --> 00:35:31,039
No.

522
00:35:32,239 --> 00:35:33,039
Nothing.

523
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:35,960
You're mad at me.

524
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,159
What do you think?

525
00:35:37,639 --> 00:35:38,840
You recklessly

526
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:41,079
pushed twelve lives into the fire.

527
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,159
Old Xie,

528
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,599
this is how your path keeps getting narrower.

529
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:48,119
Fine.

530
00:35:49,079 --> 00:35:50,280
People from the Xie family

531
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,480
should at least have this much backbone.

532
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,159
Otherwise, we don't deserve our family name.

533
00:35:55,519 --> 00:35:56,920
As long as the mission gets done,

534
00:35:57,559 --> 00:35:59,800
I can overlook your disrespect.

535
00:36:02,159 --> 00:36:03,039
What mission?

536
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:05,599
What are you planning now?

537
00:36:08,119 --> 00:36:09,639
I want Liang Shuo

538
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:12,159
to find a way to locate Asai Shou.

539
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,079
Then get rid of him.

540
00:36:17,239 --> 00:36:18,320
Get rid of him?

541
00:36:19,639 --> 00:36:20,800
What about the list?

542
00:36:21,119 --> 00:36:23,199
There's still no sign of the list.

543
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,280
That list is a ticking time bomb.

544
00:36:26,719 --> 00:36:28,559
Asai Shou is the fuse.

545
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:30,400
As long as the fuse is gone,

546
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:33,199
the bomb will never go off.

547
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:49,719
Yuxin

548
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,360
Mr. Li has left?

549
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:51,920
Yes.

550
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,079
He said there was something

551
00:36:53,079 --> 00:36:54,239
he suddenly remembered he hadn't done yet.

552
00:36:54,239 --> 00:36:54,920
So he left.

553
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:57,079
Sister-in-law,

554
00:36:57,599 --> 00:36:58,800
can I use the phone in our shop?

555
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:00,079
Can I use it for a moment?

556
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,159
Just go ahead and use it.

557
00:37:02,199 --> 00:37:03,719
No need to be so polite with me.

558
00:37:03,719 --> 00:37:04,360
Okay.

559
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,199
Hello?

560
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,199
Hello?

561
00:37:24,119 --> 00:37:25,000
Miss Xie,

562
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:26,400
I'm looking for Liang Shuo.

563
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:29,199
The boss went out with Director Cui.

564
00:37:29,199 --> 00:37:31,639
They said there's a temporary task over at Siming Alley.

565
00:37:32,119 --> 00:37:33,119
Okay, got it.

566
00:37:33,119 --> 00:37:33,840
Thank you.

567
00:37:42,239 --> 00:37:43,000
Sister-in-law

568
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:44,280
I'm heading out for a bit.

569
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,159
